abstract: Dallas Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott did not have an injury designation on the team's injury report on Friday despite being limited in practice all week.
snippet: Dallas Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott did not have an injury designation on the team's injury report on Friday despite being limited in practice all week.
lead_paragraph: Dallas Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott did not have an injury designation on the team's injury report on Friday despite being limited in practice all week.
headline_main: NFL Notebook: Cowboys' Prescott Off Injury Report, Plans to Play
headline_print_headline: NFL Notebook: Cowboys' Prescott Off Injury Report, Plans to Play

abstract: Home hero Adam Scott shot a patient three-under 69 to take a one-shot lead at the Australian PGA Championship after the third round on Saturday and raise his hopes of a second title at the A$1.5 million ($1.03 million) event on the Gold Coast.
snippet: Home hero Adam Scott shot a patient three-under 69 to take a one-shot lead at the Australian PGA Championship after the third round on Saturday and raise his hopes of a second title at the A$1.5 million ($1.03 million) event on the Gold Coast.
lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE — Home hero Adam Scott shot a patient three-under 69 to take a one-shot lead at the Australian PGA Championship after the third round on Saturday and raise his hopes of a second title at the A$1.5 million ($1.03 million) event on the Gold Coast.
headline_main: Golf: Scott Surges Into Lead at Australian PGA Championship
headline_print_headline: Golf: Scott Surges Into Lead at Australian PGA Championship

abstract: New Zealand wicketkeeper BJ Watling expects his team to continue their short-pitched barrage at the Melbourne Cricket Ground against Australia if the wicket proves conducive during the Boxing Day test.
snippet: New Zealand wicketkeeper BJ Watling expects his team to continue their short-pitched barrage at the Melbourne Cricket Ground against Australia if the wicket proves conducive during the Boxing Day test.
lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE — New Zealand wicketkeeper BJ Watling expects his team to continue their short-pitched barrage at the Melbourne Cricket Ground against Australia if the wicket proves conducive during the Boxing Day test.
headline_main: New Zealand's Watling Sees More 'Bumpers' in Melbourne
headline_print_headline: New Zealand's Watling Sees More 'Bumpers' in Melbourne

abstract: Near-simultaneous attacks believed to have been carried out by drones hit three government-run oil and gas installations in central Syria, state TV and the Oil Ministry said Saturday.
snippet: Near-simultaneous attacks believed to have been carried out by drones hit three government-run oil and gas installations in central Syria, state TV and the Oil Ministry said Saturday.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Near-simultaneous attacks believed to have been carried out by drones hit three government-run oil and gas installations in central Syria, state TV and the Oil Ministry said Saturday.
headline_main: Syria Says Possible Drone Attacks Hit 3 Oil, Gas Facilities
headline_print_headline: Syria Says Possible Drone Attacks Hit 3 Oil, Gas Facilities

abstract: Britain has approved the purchase of British defense company Cobham by U.S. investor Advent International for $5 billion after the private equity group made commitments to address national security concerns.
snippet: Britain has approved the purchase of British defense company Cobham by U.S. investor Advent International for $5 billion after the private equity group made commitments to address national security concerns.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain has approved the purchase of British defense company Cobham by U.S. investor Advent International for $5 billion after the private equity group made commitments to address national security concerns.
headline_main: Britain Gives U.S. Investor Go-Ahead to Buy Cobham for $5 Billion
headline_print_headline: Britain Gives U.S. Investor Go-Ahead to Buy Cobham for $5 Billion

abstract: Iran, Malaysia, Turkey and Qatar are considering trading among themselves in gold and through a barter system as a hedge against any future economic sanctions on them, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said on Saturday.
snippet: Iran, Malaysia, Turkey and Qatar are considering trading among themselves in gold and through a barter system as a hedge against any future economic sanctions on them, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Iran, Malaysia, Turkey and Qatar are considering trading among themselves in gold and through a barter system as a hedge against any future economic sanctions on them, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said on Saturday.
headline_main: Muslim Nations Consider Gold, Barter Trade to Beat Sanctions
headline_print_headline: Muslim Nations Consider Gold, Barter Trade to Beat Sanctions

abstract: Private equity firm Lone Star has entered a deal to buy BASF's construction chemicals business for 3.17 billion euros ($3.5 billion) on a cash and debt-free basis, the German chemicals company said on Saturday as it seeks to focus on more profitable operations.
snippet: Private equity firm Lone Star has entered a deal to buy BASF's construction chemicals business for 3.17 billion euros ($3.5 billion) on a cash and debt-free basis, the German chemicals company said on Saturday as it seeks to focus on more profitab...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Private equity firm Lone Star has entered a deal to buy BASF's construction chemicals business for 3.17 billion euros ($3.5 billion) on a cash and debt-free basis, the German chemicals company said on Saturday as it seeks to focus on more profitable operations.
headline_main: Lone Star to Buy BASF Construction Chemicals Unit for $3.51 Billion
headline_print_headline: Lone Star to Buy BASF Construction Chemicals Unit for $3.51 Billion

abstract: It is not possible for soccer to reap all of the rewards of its global ventures without acquiring some of the risk.
snippet: It is not possible for soccer to reap all of the rewards of its global ventures without acquiring some of the risk.
lead_paragraph: Mesut Özil is slowly disappearing from China. An online forum dedicated to him has closed. He has been scrubbed from the version of Pro Evolution Soccer, the video game, that is available in the country. Arsenal's last Premier League game, at home to Manchester City, was not broadcast on Chinese television. It is not clear, yet, how long the blackout will last.

abstract: Fire conditions eased on some of the major fronts burning across Australia on Sunday after a cool weather change, with firefighters trying to contain blazes before the expected return of hotter conditions at the end of the week.
snippet: Fire conditions eased on some of the major fronts burning across Australia on Sunday after a cool weather change, with firefighters trying to contain blazes before the expected return of hotter conditions at the end of the week.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY — Fire conditions eased on some of the major fronts burning across Australia on Sunday after a cool weather change, with firefighters trying to contain blazes before the expected return of hotter conditions at the end of the week.
headline_main: Australian PM Defends Climate Policies as Cooler Weather Helps Firefighters
headline_print_headline: Australian PM Defends Climate Policies as Cooler Weather Helps Firefighters

abstract: PG&E Corp's creditors have sweetened their offer to California wildfire victims, saying they are now prepared to pay $13.5 billion in cash upfront, according to a letter sent on Friday to state governor Gavin Newsom.
snippet: PG&E Corp's creditors have sweetened their offer to California wildfire victims, saying they are now prepared to pay $13.5 billion in cash upfront, according to a letter sent on Friday to state governor Gavin Newsom.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - PG&E Corp's creditors have sweetened their offer to California wildfire victims, saying they are now prepared to pay $13.5 billion in cash upfront, according to a letter sent on Friday to state governor Gavin Newsom.
headline_main: PG&E Creditors Offer California Wildfire Victims $13.5 Billion in Cash Upfront
headline_print_headline: PG&E Creditors Offer California Wildfire Victims $13.5 Billion in Cash Upfront
